       <article class="post-7 page type-page status-publish hentry" id="post-7">
        <header class="entry-header">
         <h1 class="entry-title">
          My favorite games
         </h1>
        </header>
        <!-- .entry-header -->
        <div class="entry-content">
         <p class="p1">
          <span class="s1">
           Being a full-time and passionate gamer, I used to try new games as soon as I hear about them. I cannot list all the games here because the list is too long and I don’t even remember all of their names. Isn’t that funny! But yes, it’s the fact and I am really sorry to mention it. But, there are some of the games that are my favorite and in this article, I am going to discuss some of them.
          </span>
         </p>
         <p>
         </p>
         <p class="p2">
          <span class="s1">
           <b>
            <a href="http://www.gamingwithsophie.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Counter-Strike_Logo.png">
             <img width="300" height="82" alt="Counter-Strike_Logo" src="http://www.gamingwithsophie.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Counter-Strike_Logo-300x82.png" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-39" />
            </a>
            <br />
            Half-Life: Counter-Strike
            <br />
           </b>
          </span>
          <span class="s1">
           Yes, Counter Strike tops the list of my favorites where, I get to experience the real stress and pressure of encounter and it allowed me to play devils game! I played this game on my friend’s PC for the first time that caught all of my attention and influenced me to get one version downloaded on my laptop as well. When I started playing, I wasn’t sure that it is the modified version of Half-Life with no n00bs, AWP-whores or wall hackers.
          </span>
         </p>
         <p class="p1">
          <span class="s1">
           Few rounds turned into hundreds then thousands and by the I looked at the date, it’s 2015! What I realized after playing Counter Strike is that it has become the global phenomenon and more and more people have started to play. With an opportunity to fight as a team and join different servers, Counter Strike has also allowed me to interact with people from different countries.
          </span>
         </p>
         <p class="p1">
          <span class="s1">
           In short, I can say that Counter Strike is a global platform for people to come and join hands!
          </span>
         </p>
         <p class="p1">
         </p>
         <p>
         </p>
         <p class="p2">
          <span class="s1">
           <b>
            <a href="http://www.gamingwithsophie.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/WoWlogo_transparency.png">
             <img width="300" height="122" alt="WoWlogo_transparency" src="http://www.gamingwithsophie.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/WoWlogo_transparency-300x122.png" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-42" />
            </a>
            <br />
            World of Warcraft
            <br />
           </b>
          </span>
          <span class="s1">
           I was introduced to World of Warcraft by my friend back in 2014 that kept my attention until now. Even though I have never met the heroin dealer, I suspect that sales patter is quite similar. The issue with the fame is that it’s quite interesting and I simply cannot leave playing it without any reason! For me, it has actually encapsulated the required attribute of massive multiplayer online games.
          </span>
         </p>
         <p class="p2">
          <span class="s1">
           <b>
            <br />
            <a href="http://www.gamingwithsophie.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/diablo_ii_logo_render_by_digitaleva-d37dszc.png">
             <img width="300" height="149" alt="diablo_ii_logo_render_by_digitaleva-d37dszc" src="http://www.gamingwithsophie.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/diablo_ii_logo_render_by_digitaleva-d37dszc-300x149.png" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-43" />
            </a>
            <br />
            Diablo II
            <br />
           </b>
          </span>
          <span class="s1">
           Since I love action games, Diablo II is another game that got my attention and become one of my favorite games with its early 1997 scary bejesus late-night RPGs. Combined with Battle.Net (buggy hacker’s delight), I have experienced a new dimension of action games due to which, I used to recommend this game to my friends as well. Its satanic-sounding electronic box set and demonic possession are other fascinating factors for my gaming nature that helped me to realize my skills and efficiency in playing action games.
          </span>
         </p>
         <p class="p2">
          <span class="s1">
           <b>
            <br />
            <a href="http://www.gamingwithsophie.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Civ_V_logo.jpg">
             <img width="300" height="92" alt="Civ_V_logo" src="http://www.gamingwithsophie.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Civ_V_logo-300x92.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-44" />
            </a>
            <br />
            Sid Meier’s Civilization
            <br />
           </b>
          </span>
          <span class="s1">
           With lots of suspense and turn-based strategies, Sid Meier’s Civilization is at forth in my list. Apart from its trifling gameplay problems, I have not found the same level of addictiveness in other games. It’s graphics, performance and strategies used, in short, everything is really amazing yet simple.
          </span>
         </p>
         <p class="p2">
          <span class="s1">
           <b>
            <br />
            <a href="http://www.gamingwithsophie.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Logo_Dota_2.png">
             <img width="300" height="62" alt="Logo_Dota_2" src="http://www.gamingwithsophie.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Logo_Dota_2-300x62.png" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-45" />
            </a>
            <br />
            Dota
            <br />
           </b>
          </span>
          <span class="s1">
           Last but not the least, Dota also comes in my list with its amazing graphics and sound effects. It was referred by one of my friends. When I look at its images, I wasn’t sure about its performance but when I tried it, my views got changed and I became addicted to it.
          </span>
         </p>
        </div>
        <!-- .entry-content -->
       </article>
